Okay-

This morning I took my coil, condenser, points, rotor, cap, and spark plug
leads from my working bus, and transplanted them into the '73. No change.

Jay's message below got me thinking though, and out of desperation, I
started messing with my point gap. I found that if I gapped them to 0.030",
18 Deg dwell (!) it ran reasonably well. WTF?

So, it seems to me that this is a timing issue. What could have happened to
cause this? Will timing the engine just be masking an existing problem? How
do I best time my engine as it will not idle with proper point gap?

Thanks for your help.

